  "textResponse": "Here are some of the **top AI-related headlines for Thursday, April 9, 2026**, based on recent and same-day coverage I could verify:\n\n- **OpenAI plans a new cybersecurity-focused product** — Axios reported that OpenAI is preparing a new product aimed at cybersecurity use cases, following heightened concern across the industry about increasingly capable AI systems being used for offensive hacking tasks. ([axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2026/04/09/openai-new-model-cyber-mythos-anthopic?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Anthropic expands infrastructure deals as AI demand rises** — Multiple reports this week say Anthropic is deepening its chip and compute partnerships with Google and Broadcom, including access to large amounts of TPU capacity starting in 2027, a sign of growing demand for Claude and related services. ([tomshardware.com](https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/broadcom-expands-anthropic-deal-to-3-5gw-of-google-tpu-capacity-from-2027?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **AI safety and national-security tensions remain a major story** — Recent reporting has continued to focus on government concern over advanced model capabilities, especially around cyber risk and military use. That includes earlier U.S. government action involving Anthropic and subsequent movement by agencies toward rival providers such as OpenAI and Google. ([apnews.com](https://apnews.com/article/b72d1894bc842d9acf026df3867bee8a?utm_source=openai))\n\nA quick note: today’s verifiable same-day AI headline I found most clearly was the **Axios/OpenAI cybersecurity** story. The other items are the most prominent **very recent** AI headlines from the last few days, rather than all being published today specifically. ([axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2026/04/09/openai-new-model-cyber-mythos-anthopic?utm_source=openai))\n\nIf you want, I can also give you this in one of these formats:\n1. **5-bullet daily AI news brief**\n2. **Only headlines from major outlets like Reuters/AP/The Verge/TechCrunch**\n3. **Startup/investor-focused AI news only**",
